How the alcohol industry is helping combat coronavirus A rum distillery in Puerto Rico is donating the supply to hospitals.
Bottles of hand sanitizer made at the Eight Oaks Farm Distillery fill a box at the distillery in New Tripoli, Pa., March 16, 2020.
The distillery's owner, Chad Butters, grew increasingly angry as he saw the skyrocketing price of hand sanitizer.
Matt Rourke/APThe distillation process can vary depending on the booze or the brand, but it all boils down to the same result -- alcohol.
The gin stills of the Listoke Distillery have been repurposed in the fight against the coronavirus, producing precious hand sanitizer currently in short supply across Ireland.